18 Apr 2015 Ghana: WHO official says Ebola remains threat to Ghana
http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2015-04/18/c_134160916.htm
[A World Health Organization official (Magdalene Rabalo a WHO country director) said Ghana is at risk for an Ebola outbreak. Risk factors include Ghana's porous borders, people now eating bats (a major transmitter of the Ebola virus), and the practice of shaking hands during social events which could easily spread the virus]

18 Apr 2015 Ghana: to have infectious disease centre
http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/health/artikel.php?ID=354976
[The center will provide services, training and research on infectious disease]

16 Apr 2015 Guinea: finds 9 new Ebola cases near border with Sierra Leone
http://www.reuters.com/article/2015/04/16/us-health-ebola-guinea-idUSKBN0N71TO20150416?rpc=401
[At least 9 new cases of Ebola were found in the southwest region of Forecariah near the border with Sierra Leone, confirmed by Guinean authorities. The new cases were found during a 4-day door-to-door campaign in Forecariah on 12 Apr 2015, which reached 92 percent of households. There are also 10 suspicious deaths; only 1 has been confirmed]

26 Mar 2015 India: Quarantined Indian discharged after Ebola scare
http://www.newkerala.com/news/2015/fullnews-36647.html
[This young man had been isolated at a special facility at the Delhi airport since November 2014 before being discharged earlier this week, according to Health Ministry sources. He had been treated for the disease in Liberia and had no symptoms. But his semen samples tested positive, presumably for viral RNA only, prompting the authorities to isolate him. - Mod.LK]

16 Apr 2015 Liberia : Ebola-hit rebuilds devastated child health-care system
http://www.timeslive.co.za/africa/2015/04/16/ebola-hit-liberia-rebuilds-devastated-child-healthcare-system
[Medecins Sans Frontieres' recently opened 46-bed facility in Monrovia is the 1st children's hospital in the nation]

16 Apr 2015: Liberia: In Ebola audit report - internal affairs ministry, others 'hooked'
http://allafrica.com/stories/201504161574.html?viewall=1

17 Apr 2015 Liberia: "Exhausted" Liberia struggles with long Ebola 'to do' list http://allafrica.com/stories/201504171855.html?viewall=1
["It's not rocket science, (we need) a community health worker for every village. We need to change our bias against remote areas of this planet. That's what really bit us" - Chief executive of Last Mile Health charity Raj Panjab.]

16 Apr 2015 Sierra Leone: Free media helps beat down Ebola in Sierra Leone
http://allafrica.com/stories/201504171779.html?viewall=1
[Hundreds of hard-to-reach communities in Sierra Leone, in urgent need of information, now get Ebola advice and independent news thanks to a new satellite link from the United Nations Development Programme (UNDP). This increases the reach of Sierra Leone's only free radio network, Independent Radio Network (IRN)]

17 Apr 2015 Liberia: MSF hands over ELWA 3 to the Liberian Ministry of Health
http://www.msf.org/article/liberia-msf-hands-over-elwa-3-liberian-ministry-health
[The Liberian Health Ministry will run the 30-bed facility as a temporary Ebola management center]

17 Apr 2015 Sierra Leone: Behind closed doors: Schools, teenage girls and Ebola in Sierra Leone
http://www.africaresearchinstitute.org/blog/behind-closed-doors-schools-teenage-girls-and-ebola-in-sierra-leone

16 Apr 2015 Sierra Leone: Kroo Bay quarantined homes Ebola free
http://allafrica.com/stories/201504171048.html?viewall=1
[The Kroo Bay slum community recorded a new Ebola case in April 2015. As a result, authorities quarantined many households to stem the spread of the virus. The 21-day quarantine was over last Sun 12 Apr 2015]

16 Apr 2015 Sierra Leone: Pregnant girls in Sierra Leone not allowed back to school due to 'bad moral example'
http://allafrica.com/stories/201504161272.html
[But see previous update -- Unicef & others trying to get them to be allowed to take important exams. - Mod.JW]

16 Apr 2015 Slovenia: suspect of Ebola tested negative
http://en.apa.az/-_225839.html
[Preliminary test was normal]
And the follow-up confirmation:
19 Apr 2015: Slovenian febrile patient cleared of Ebola suspicion
http://en.apa.az/-_225927.html
[2 tests for Ebola virus were negative. Patient will be discharged from the hospital]

16 Apr 2015 UK: Bognor Regis Hospital in shutdown after Ebola scare
http://www.itv.com/news/meridian/update/2015-04-16/bognor-regis-hospital-in-shutdown-after-ebola-scare/
[Bognor Regis Hospital is located in West Sussex, UK. A person arrived at the Minor Injuries Unit with a possible infectious disease. The facility was closed down temporarily, but reopened at the advice of Public Health England]

17 Apr 2015 USA (Texas): Synthetic pot blamed for death of US soldier deployed to Ebola zone
http://www.cbsnews.com/news/synthetic-pot-blamed-for-death-of-fort-hood-soldier-deployed-to-ebola-zone/
[Soldier was stationed at Fort Hood, Texas, USA]
[The soldier had helped construct an Ebola treatment camp, but had not had contact with patients. A dramatic spike in hospital visits for synthetic marijuana-related emergencies has been observed in a number of states in the US. - Mod.LK]

