19 Apr 2015 ADB: USD 300 million from African Development Bank to support post-Ebola recovery programs
http://www.eturbonews.com/57826/300-million-african-development-bank-support-post-ebola-recovery?utm_source=feedburner&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=Feed%3A+Eturbonews-TravelAndTourismIndustryNews+%28eTurboNews+-+for+the+global+travel+professional%29
[Funding will provide support to governments of Ebola-affected countries by investing in health, education, water and sanitation, agriculture and financial sectors. In addition to USD 523 million to strengthen the health and transport sector, the Bank is currently preparing 2 new post Ebola operations]

17 Apr 2015 ICRC: donates trucks to help Liberia dislodge Ebola waste
http://allafrica.com/stories/201504170872.html?viewall=1
[ICRC = The International Committee of the Red Cross. 2 state-of-the-art trucks were donated to the Liberia Water and Sewer Corporation for the dislodging of liquid waste from Ebola Treatment Units]

