18 Apr 2015 USA: Paul Allen joins battle against Ebola with money, movies
http://www.cnbc.com/id/102594826
[Allen (Microsoft co-founder) has already pledged USD 100 million to combat Ebola. In addition, he funded a short movie ("Body Team 12"), through his own production company, Vulcan Productions, in partnership with RYOT Films. The movie is about a team of Liberian Red Cross workers tasked with removing bodies during the height of the Ebola crisis, and debuts on Sunday (19 Apr 2015] at the Tribeca Film Festival. Mr. Allen is worth at least USD17.5 billion]

