17 Apr 2015 W. Africa: Ebola-hit West Africa unveils USD 8 billion recovery plan
http://www.trust.org/item/20150417172546-3tuph/
[Referencing the Marshall Plan (in which approximately USD 120 billion in present-day value was given to help rebuild European economies after World War II), the 3 West African countries hit worse by the Ebola virus disease outbreak unveiled the USD-8-billion recovery plan on Fri 17 Apr 2015. The countries' leadership also asked for urgent international assistance in rebuilding health-care systems, feeding their people, and new-job creation. The countries' leaders say they need the 1st half within 2 years]

17 Apr 2015: W. Africa: Ebola-hit West African countries press for debt cancellation
